        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 5:38PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 534 PM EDT, amateur radio operators reported dime sized hail in
the Knoxville area, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Amateur radio.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Knoxville, Sevierville, Pigeon Forge, McMahan, Lake Forest,
Harrisburg, Fairgarden, Seymour, and Kimberlin Heights.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
